<p itemprop="description">A head of test is responsible for testing strategy and quality assurance across an entire organisation. They establish organisational testing capability, lead transformation in quality practices, and work at executive level to ensure digital services meet the highest standards of quality and user experience.</p>

<section class="role-details">
    <h2>Typical responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Define and implement organisational testing strategy and quality frameworks</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Lead testing capability transformation and establish quality maturity</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Work with executive leadership on strategic quality and risk initiatives</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Manage organisational testing budgets, resources, and capability development</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Drive innovation and continuous improvement in testing and quality practices</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Influence policy and strategic direction through testing and quality expertise</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Establish organisational testing standards and governance frameworks</li>
    </ul>
</section>

